cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.SD

Reasoning: 
- cs.AI is the most likely category as the paper introduces a fully automatic method for video game level generation using the GVG-AI framework and the Constrained MAP-Elites algorithm.
- cs.GR (Graphics) is also likely as the paper deals with generating tile-based levels for video games.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the Constrained MAP-Elites algorithm is a machine learning technique.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve image processing techniques for analyzing game levels.
- cs.SD (Sound) is unlikely as the paper does not mention anything related to sound.
